verbose_text: Overexpression of sox3 and pax3 in anatomical positions of the chordoneural hinge and the posterior wall of the neurenteric canal reflects the local shift of neuromesodermal identity in T-box TF depleted embryos, such that the loss of axial and paraxial mesoderm is accompanied by the gain of ventrolateral and dorsal neural tissue, respectively (XREF_FIG Biii).
